Give Me Some Credit¶

Competition on Kaggle. Goal is to improve on the state of the art in credit scoring by predicting the probability that somebody will experience financial distress in the next two years.

  • The data preparation I did in R. See PreparacionDatos.R
  • See FirstDataAnalysis.html and DimensionalityReduction.html for more details

df.Income.isnull().sum()
Out[3]:
29731
In [4]:
# Dropping SD
X = df.drop('SD', axis=1)

# Indexing NA's
NoIncome = X.Income.isnull()

# Making a traning set of rows with income
X_train = X[NoIncome == False].drop('Income', axis=1)
y_train = X[NoIncome == False].Income

# Making a set to predict on
X_impute = X[NoIncome == True].drop('Income', axis=1)
In [5]:
# Doing linear regression to predict Income
model = LinearRegression(normalize=True)
model.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_hat = model.predict(X_impute)
In [6]:
df.loc[NoIncome == True, 'Income'] = y_hat
df.to_csv('../dat/Train2.csv', index=False)
In [7]:
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
scores = cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=5, scoring='r2')
scores
Out[7]:
array([0.33826844, 0.3321081 , 0.32236518, 0.33865509, 0.33602746])
In [8]:
# Doing the same for the Test set
df = pd.read_csv('../dat/Test1.csv', sep=',') # Train3 are centralized & scaled data
X = df.drop('id', axis=1)

# Indexing NA's
NoIncome = X.Income.isnull()

# Making a traning set of rows with income
X_train = X[NoIncome == False].drop('Income', axis=1)
y_train = X[NoIncome == False].Income

# Making a set to predict on
X_impute = X[NoIncome == True].drop('Income', axis=1)
model.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_hat = model.predict(X_impute)

df.loc[NoIncome == True, 'Income'] = y_hat
df.to_csv('../dat/Test2.csv', index=False)

Data preparation continues in PreparacionDatos.R

Cross Validation to see which kernel & parameters are best¶

In [38]:
# CV
tuned_parameters = [{'kernel': ['rbf'], 'C': [1, 0.5, 0.1, 0.05, 0.001]},
                    {'kernel': ['linear'], 'C': [1]}]

clf = GridSearchCV(SVC(probability=True), tuned_parameters, cv=5, scoring='roc_auc')
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
Out[38]:
GridSearchCV(cv=5, error_score='raise',
       estimator=SVC(C=1.0, cache_size=200, class_weight=None, coef0=0.0,
  decision_function_shape='ovr', degree=3, gamma='auto', kernel='rbf',
  max_iter=-1, probability=True, random_state=None, shrinking=True,
  tol=0.001, verbose=False),
       fit_params=None, iid=True, n_jobs=1,
       param_grid=[{'kernel': ['rbf'], 'C': [1, 0.5, 0.1, 0.05, 0.001]}, {'kernel': ['linear'], 'C': [1]}],
       pre_dispatch='2*n_jobs', refit=True, return_train_score=True,
       scoring='roc_auc', verbose=0)

In [40]:
print("Grid scores on training set:")
print()
means = clf.cv_results_['mean_test_score']
stds = clf.cv_results_['std_test_score']
for mean, std, params in zip(means, stds, clf.cv_results_['params']):
    print("%0.3f (+/-%0.03f) for %r"
          % (mean, std * 2, params))

Grid scores on training set:

0.843 (+/-0.011) for {'C': 1, 'kernel': 'rbf'}
0.844 (+/-0.011) for {'C': 0.5, 'kernel': 'rbf'}
0.847 (+/-0.010) for {'C': 0.1, 'kernel': 'rbf'}
0.847 (+/-0.010) for {'C': 0.05, 'kernel': 'rbf'}
0.829 (+/-0.007) for {'C': 0.001, 'kernel': 'rbf'}
0.851 (+/-0.011) for {'C': 1, 'kernel': 'linear'}

The AUC score of 0.843 is different than above, but CV shows that the linear kernel is better.

# Import balanced data
df = pd.read_csv('../dat/Train4.csv', sep=',')

# Getting predictors/target
predictors = df.drop(['SD'], axis=1).as_matrix()
target = to_categorical(df.SD)
In [54]:
# Specify the model
n_cols = predictors.shape[1]
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu', input_shape = (n_cols,)))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(2, activation='softmax'))

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Early stopping
early_stopping_monitor = EarlyStopping(patience=2)

# Fit the model
model_train = model.fit(predictors, target, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_split=0.2,
                        callbacks=[early_stopping_monitor])

In [62]:
# Using dropout

df = pd.read_csv('../dat/Train4.csv', sep=',')
predictors = df.drop(['SD'], axis=1).as_matrix()
target = to_categorical(df.SD)

model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu', input_shape = (n_cols,)))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(2, activation='softmax'))

model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

early_stopping_monitor = EarlyStopping(patience=2)

model_train = model.fit(predictors, target, epochs=10, batch_size=64, validation_split=0.2,
                        callbacks=[early_stopping_monitor])

In [65]:
# Import training data
df = pd.read_csv('../dat/Train3.csv', sep=',')

# Getting predictors/target
predictors = df.drop(['SD'], axis=1).as_matrix()
target = to_categorical(df.SD)

# Specify the model
n_cols = predictors.shape[1]
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu', input_shape = (n_cols,)))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(2, activation='softmax'))

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Early stopping
early_stopping_monitor = EarlyStopping(patience=2)

# Fit the model
model_train = model.fit(predictors, target, epochs=5, batch_size=64, validation_split=0.2,
                        callbacks=[early_stopping_monitor])

# Save the model
model.save('../mod/model_NN2_file.h5')

Train on 120000 samples, validate on 30000 samples

submission = pd.DataFrame()
submission['Id'] = X_test.id
submission['Probability'] = model.predict_proba(X_test.drop('id', axis=1))[:,1]
submission.to_csv("../sub/entryXGB.csv", index=False)
# Kaggle Private Score: 0.864961 < 0.865048 (NN2)

Stacking different models¶

In [22]:
# Import balanced data
df = pd.read_csv('../dat/Train4.csv', sep=',')
X = df.drop('SD', axis=1)
y = df.SD

# Split train/test
X_train, X_validation, y_train, y_validation = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.85, random_state=1234)

Ensemble = pd.DataFrame()

# LR
model1 = LogisticRegression(random_state=42)
model1.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_hat = model1.predict_proba(X_validation)[:,1]
Ensemble['P1'] = y_hat

# SVM
model2 = SVC(kernel='linear', probability=True, random_state=42, verbose=False)
model2.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_hat = model2.predict_proba(X_validation)[:,1]
Ensemble['P2'] = y_hat

# Import NN2 model
model3 = load_model('../mod/model_NN2_file.h5')
y_hat = model3.predict(X_validation)[:,1]
Ensemble['P3'] = y_hat

# XGB
model4 = XGBClassifier()
model4.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_hat = model4.predict_proba(X_validation)[:,1]
Ensemble['P4'] = y_hat

# CatBoost
model5 = CatBoostClassifier(use_best_model=True, random_seed=42)
model5.fit(X_train, y_train, eval_set=(X_validation, y_validation), plot=False)
y_hat = model5.predict(X_validation, prediction_type='Probability')[:,1]
Ensemble['P5'] = y_hat

X_test['P3'] = pd.read_csv('../sub/entryNN2.csv', sep=',')['Probability']
X_test['P4'] = pd.read_csv('../sub/entryXGB.csv', sep=',')['Probability']
X_test['P5'] = pd.read_csv('../sub/CatBoost.csv', sep=',')['Probability']
submisstion = pd.DataFrame()
submisstion['Id'] = X_test.Id
submisstion['Probability'] = model6.predict_proba(X_test.drop('Id', axis=1))[:,1]
submisstion.to_csv("../sub/entryStack.csv", index=False)

Ensemble of NN2 & CatBoost¶

In [24]:
# Ensemble
submission = pd.read_csv('../sub/entryNN2.csv', sep=',')
submission.rename(columns={'Probability': 'P1'}, inplace=True)
submission['P2'] = pd.read_csv('../sub/CatBoost.csv', sep=',')['Probability']

# Taking the average of the predicted probabilities
submission['Probability'] = submission.drop('Id', axis=1).mean(axis = 1)
submission.drop(['P1', 'P2'], axis=1, inplace=True)
submission.to_csv("../sub/Ensemble.csv", index=False)
# Kaggle Private Score: 0.866615
